# API Reference

## Authentication

All API requests require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header.

```http
GET /api/v2/users
Authorization: Bearer <your-token>
Content-Type: application/json
```

W> Tokens expire after 24 hours. Use the refresh endpoint to obtain a new token.

## Endpoints

### GET /api/v2/users

Returns a list of users.

**Query Parameters:**

page
: The page number (default: 1)

per_page
: Number of results per page (default: 20, max: 100)

sort
: Sort field (`name`, `created_at`, `email`)

**Response:**

```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "usr_123",
      "name": "Alice",
      "email": "alice@example.com"
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "per_page": 20,
    "total": 142
  }
}
```

### POST /api/v2/users

Create a new user.

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "name": "Bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "role": "member"
}
```

**Status Codes:**

| Code | Meaning |
| ---: | --- |
| 201 | User created successfully |
| 400 | Validation error |
| 401 | Unauthorized |
| 409 | Email already exists |

### DELETE /api/v2/users/:id

Delete a user by ID.

X> This action is irreversible. All user data will be permanently deleted.

## Rate Limiting

The API enforces rate limits per token:

| Plan | Requests/min | Requests/day |
| --- | ---: | ---: |
| Free | 60 | 10000 |
| Pro | 600 | 100000 |
| Enterprise | 6000 | 1000000 |

N> Rate limit headers are included in every response: `X-RateLimit-Remaining` and `X-RateLimit-Reset`.
